<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780435>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., habitus in lateral view, showing colouration in fresh condition.A, holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113; B, paratype, female (cl 3.5 mm), CBM-ZC 17115; C, paratype, male (cl 3.1 mm), CBM- ZC 17117; D, paratype, ovigerous female (cl 3.5 mm), CBM-ZC 17119." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780435/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780437>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113. carapace, pleon, uropod and telson, left lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780437/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780439>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., A–D, holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113; E, paratype, male (cl 3.1 mm), CBM-ZC 17116. A, anterior part of carapace and cephalic appendages, dorsal view; B, same, left lateral view; C, left uropod, dorsal view, perpendicular to horizontal plane (setae omitted); D, telson, dorsal view; E, appendices masculina and interna of left pleopod 2, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780439/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780441>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113. A, right mandible, outer view; B, same, dorsal view; C, same, ventral view; D, right maxillule, lateral view; E, right maxilla, lateral view; F, left maxilliped 1, lateral view; G, left maxilliped 2, lateral view H, left maxilliped 3, lateral view; I, same, ultimate segment, mesial view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780441/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780443>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113. A, major (left) cheliped (pereopod1), lateral view; B, minor (right) cheliped (pereopod 1), lateral view, C, left pereopod 2, lateral view; D, right pereopod 3, lateral view; E, same, distal part of propodus and dactylus, lateral view; F, left pereopod 4, lateral view; G, same, distal part of propodus and dactylus, lateral view; H, left pereopod 5, lateral view; I, same, distal part of propodus and dactylus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780443/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780446>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp., holotype, ovigerous female (cl 3.8 mm), CBM-ZC 17113. A, chela of major (left) cheliped (pereopod 1), flexor view; B, same, extensor view; C, chela of minor (right) cheliped (pereopod 1), flexor view; D, same, extensor view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780446/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780448>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Pebble beach of Higashi-makado, Numazu City, Shizuoka Prefecture, where specimens of Metabetaeus lapillicola n. sp. were collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7780450>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Phylogenetic tree for four species of Metabetaeus and Salmoneus aduncus Komai, 2022 used as an outgroup taxon; obtained by ML analysis of 16S rRNA gene sequences using the TIM3+I substitution model. The best tree with the highest log likelihood (-1856.260992) is shown. Bootstrap values of higher than 70% are indicated at nodes as percentage values.There was a total of 386 bp in the final dataset trimmed with Gblocks." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7780450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

